        "",
        "<h1 id=\"Objective\">Objective</h1>\n\n<p>Define the function <code>halve : int list -&gt; (int list * int list)</code> that takes in a list as an argument and cuts it in half. In the case of an odd-length list, the middle element stays on the rightmost list.</p>\n<p>As an example, <code>halve [1;2;3;4;5;6;7;8;9] = ([1;2;3;4],[5;6;7;8;9])</code>.</p>\n<p>It is important to note that there is a solution that uses an auxiliary tail recursive function (with the same parameter configuration as <code>halve</code>), that only needs to run through the complete list and its first half once.</p>\n"
      ]
